      • direction

        GraphConfigurator<V,E> direction(Comparator<V> lowToHigh)
        This method sets a comparator to determine the direction of an edge between two vertices. Vertices are passed to the comparator in the order they were given when defining the edge. The default behaviour, if no comparator is specified is as if a comparator has been specified which always returns 1.
        Parameters:
        lowToHigh - A vertex comparator defining a direction between vertices
        Returns:
        A derived configurator with the requested configuration

      • direction

        GraphConfigurator<V,E> direction(Function<E,Comparator<V>> lowToHigh)
        This method accepts a function to create a comparator from an edge, over the vertices associated with that edge. The result of the application of this comparator will be used to determine the direction of that edge, with the semantics described by the direction(Comparator) method. The function is only applied at most once per creation of an edge.
        Parameters:
        lowToHigh - A function from an edge between two vertices to a vertex comparator defining a direction between those vertices
        Returns:
        A derived configurator with the requested configuration

      • edgeFactory

        <F extends E> GraphConfigurator<V,F> edgeFactory(Function<EdgeVertices<V>,F> factory)
        For simple or multigraphs, specify the mechanism by which edge objects will be generated between two vertices when an edge is added between them.

        The provided function will be invoked when an edge is added between two vertices without an edge object being explicitly provided.

        If no edge factory is provided, by way of either this method or edgeMultiFactory(Function), edge objects must be explicitly provided when adding an edge between vertices, by way of e.g. edge(Object, Object, Object) or edges(Map). Conversely, if an edge factory is provided, it will not be possible to add edges in that manner.

      • edgeMultiFactory

        <F extends E> GraphConfigurator<V,F> edgeMultiFactory(Function<EdgeVertices<V>,Set<F>> factory)
        For multigraphs, specify the mechanism by which edge objects will be generated between two vertices when an edge is added between them.

        The provided function will be invoked when an edge is added between two vertices without an edge object being explicitly provided.

        If no edge factory is provided, by way of either this method or edgeMultiFactory(Function), edge objects must be explicitly provided when adding an edge between vertices, by way of e.g. edge(Object, Object, Object) or edges(Map). Conversely, if an edge factory is provided, it will not be possible to add edges in that manner.

      • internalListeners

        GraphConfigurator<V,E> internalListeners(Consumer<GraphListeners<V,E>> internalListeners)
        Graph operations are atomic. Only one atomic operation at a time can hold a write lock in order to execute, though an atomic operation can invoke other such operations internally, and they will be considered a part of the same atomic transaction which began at some 'root' operation invocation.

        If an exception is caught at the root invocation of an atomic operation, the operation will be cancelled and all pending changes discarded. Internal listeners are triggered during an atomic operation as each change occurs, and so any exceptions they throw may propagate down in this manner.

        Returns:
        A derived configurator with the requested configuration
